bh: Backyard Birdhouse
	summary=Three friends — Mia, Leo, Aria — build a birdhouse over one week.

forsparrows: Build it for sparrows
	summary=Size the house and entrance for small sparrows. (Replaced on Day 3.)
intree: Hang it in the apple tree
	summary=Mount the finished house on a branch of the apple tree. (Replaced on Day 4.)
weatherproof: Must survive the rain
	summary=The house has to stay dry inside through a rainstorm.

q1: What color should we paint it?
a1: Mia gathers the wood
a2: Leo finds the tools

slantroof: Give it a slanted roof
	summary=A sloped roof so rain runs off instead of pooling.
a3: Aria cuts the panels
q2: How big should the entrance hole be?

forbluebirds: Build it for bluebirds
	summary=Switch the target bird from sparrows to bluebirds.
hole15: A 1.5-inch entrance hole
	summary=The hole size that fits bluebirds.
d_panels: Cut wood panels
a4: Leo assembles the box

d_box: Assembled birdhouse box
tooheavy: The box is too heavy for the tree branch
	summary=The assembled box would bend or snap a thin apple-tree branch.
onfence: Mount it on the fence post
	summary=Attach the house to the sturdy fence post instead of the tree.
paintblue: Paint it blue
	summary=Blue paint to match the bluebirds.
a5: Mia paints the birdhouse

d_house: Finished painted birdhouse
a6: Aria mounts it on the fence post
q3: Will the birds actually come?
